    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Hey there! I\u2019m selling my absolute pride and joy, and honestly, she\u2019s a total dream. This car has been babied since day one\u2014always kept in the garage and maintained in such pristine condition that it still has that new-car feel. It looks and drives like it just rolled off the showroom floor! If you\u2019re looking for a ride that\u2019s basically flawless and ready for a new home, this is the one. Come take a look, you won\u2019t be disappointed!",
      "price": 46500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 7
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) finished in Alpine White over Cinnamon Nappa leather. This example features the iconic S54 3.2L inline-six, utilizing individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure double-VANOS system to deliver a linear 8,000 RPM redline. The Getrag 6-speed manual transmission provides tactile engagement, paired with a factory M-Variable limited-slip differential. Critical preventative maintenance is complete, including rod bearing replacement and proactive rear subframe reinforcement. The chassis remains factory-stiff with no oxidation, riding on original Style 67 forged wheels. This is a turn-key, investment-grade specimen for the discerning purist.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 7
    },
    {
